                  </app>
                   <app loc="12-13">
                     <lem>nr̥penāpi</lem>
                     <rdg source="bib:Pou2001_01">sr̥pa nā pi</rdg>
                      <note>A similar stanza portion is found in the inscription <ref target="K0379.xml">K. 379</ref> from Prasat Krabas (10th century; <bibl><ptr target="bib:Coedes1937-1966_01"/><citedRange unit="volume">6</citedRange><citedRange unit="page">213</citedRange></bibl>; st. III): <foreign>tad ahāryyaṇ nr̥penāpi kim utaḥ svattavāndhavaiḥ</foreign>. But the epigraph, considered too erroneous, was not translated by Cœdès.</note>
                  </app>
               </listApp>
